statement.p:
Consider functions f:{\left\{1,2,3\right\}} \to {\left\{0,1,2,3,4\right\}}\text{.} 




How many of these functions are strictly increasing? Explain. (A function is strictly increasing provided if \renewcommand{\v}{\vtx{above}{}}a \lt   b\text{,} then \renewcommand{\v}{\vtx{above}{}}f(a) \lt   f(b)\text{.})






How many of the functions are non-decreasing? Explain. (A function is non-decreasing provided if \renewcommand{\v}{\vtx{above}{}}a \lt   b\text{,} then f(a) \le f(b)\text{.})

